The use of deep-water traps in Guam and the rest of the Mariana Is have already uncovered many new and/or rare species of homolids, poupiniids, inachids and mathildellids (
Eldredge 1980
;
Williams & Moffitt 1991
;
Ng & Wang 2002
;
Crosnier & Ng 2004
). The present discovery of
Calappa karenae
sp. nov.
attests to the value of using trapping in areas with deep steep cliffs which cannot be sampled by trawls or dredges (see
Mendoza et al. 2010
).
